    <item>
      <title>Standalone Elemental Weapons</title>
      <author>Real Princess Zelda</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/515182</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/515182#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">459789089ee3847394a1920cee0d76d2c70a9cc0</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 01 Dec 2024 04:02:05 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/665ebf6a8977a.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/665ec267a7edf.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/664e549879bd8.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/664e549b21617.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/664e54a585a6e.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/665651d2e44ff.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/664e54944b888.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/665651d66a3c0.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/665ebf84f3c77.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/665ebf88c2daa.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/665ebf8f7af8c.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/664e54b0a6da3.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/664e54ad451aa.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/664e54b3db906.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/665651fd62301.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6656520289b10.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6656520a593b4.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/665ebfb609af4.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/665ebfbabec8b.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/665ebfc119505.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; Rock Octorok + Compendium Fix&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;I have now made it so the weapons can be repaired and given a modifier if eaten by a rock octorok. The exefs file within fixes a bug that crashes the game after the credits when the compendium entries are more than 509 (which is the amount in the base game). Thanks so much to &lt;a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="https://gamebanana.com/members/1771411"&gt;Echocolat&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="https://github.com/dt-12345"&gt;dt-12345&lt;/a&gt; for making the fix and allowing me to use it.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Addition&lt;/em&gt;: All weapons can now be repaired and given a modifier via rock octoroks&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Bugfix&lt;/em&gt;: Added exefs file that fixes a crash after the credits because of too many compendium entries&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Do you miss the weapons of Breath of the Wild? Do you find the frostblade so slick and cool? Do you want dedicated elemental weapons that look unique and cool? Are you suffering from a dash of nostalgia?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;Well, now you can have those elemental weapons from BotW as their own standalone weapons! Princess Zelda herself has worked with the wonderful &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/members/1681024"&gt;Lye&lt;/a&gt; to make her amazing elemental weapons standalone! This adds all of the elemental weapons from BotW as standalones.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;What this does:&lt;/span&gt; Adds the great frostblade, great flameblade, great thunderblade, frostblade, flameblade, thunderblade, frostspear, flamespear, and thunderspear as standalone weapons obtainable in the world (or Amiibo if you take the optional file). To achieve the particle effects from swinging your weapon, increase the damage of the blades, or apply the blades on other weapons, we also added the blades only as an attachable material sold in a few Beedle shops. The weapons are part of the compendium and level (gain weapon modifiers).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;There is now a breakable weapons option! The Great Frostblade has 40 durability, the Great Flameblade &amp;amp; Thunderblade have 50 durability. The Frostspear has 40 durability, the Flamespear &amp;amp; Thunderspear have 50 durability. Then, the Frostblade has 30 durability, the Flameblade &amp;amp; Thunderblade has 36 durability.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;The blade attachments are located in Beedle's shop inventory. The &#13;
frost blade attachments can be bought from Snowfield Stable, the flame &#13;
blade attachments from Foothill Stable, and the thunder blade &#13;
attachments are bought from the Riverside Stable. They are all purchasable for 40 rupees each.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Where to find:&lt;/span&gt; The weapons are scattered throughout the map, here are the locations listed below&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;Flameblade &amp;amp; Thunderblade:&lt;/b&gt; Found within Hyrule castle on the surface. Coordinates &lt;span class="Spoiler"&gt;-0268, 1153, 0024 &amp;amp; -0254, 0759, 0104&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Frostblade:&lt;/b&gt; Atop Mount Lanayru embedded in ice. Coordinates &lt;span class="Spoiler"&gt;3942, -1260, 0490&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Great Flameblade:&lt;/b&gt; Lost in a maze within the Akkala region. Coordinates &lt;span class="Spoiler"&gt;4662, 3701, 0115&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Great Thunderblade:&lt;/b&gt; Partially buried atop Cuho Mountain. Coordinates &lt;span class="Spoiler"&gt;-3832, 1324, 0251&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Great Frostblade:&lt;/b&gt; Resting on the peak of the Hebra Mountains. Coordinates &lt;span class="Spoiler"&gt;-2765, 2908, 0724&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Flamespear:&lt;/b&gt; Overlooking Eventide Island. Coordinates &lt;span class="Spoiler"&gt;3688, -3319, 0244&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Thunderspear:&lt;/b&gt; Resting near Thundra Plateau. Coordinates: &lt;span class="Spoiler SelectedElement"&gt;-2244, 0836, 0105&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Frostspear:&lt;/b&gt; Surrounded by ponds southwest from Hateno Village. Coordinates &lt;span class="Spoiler"&gt;2696, -2963, 0168&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Compatibility:&lt;/span&gt; This mod modifies the RSDB, RSTB, and Mals files as well as a few map files and three Beedle shop inventories, and it modifies the ResidentCommon and Bootup.Nin_NX_NVN pack files. It also modifies several map files. You will need to merge them for compatibility. This should work on versions 1.1.0, 1.1.1, 1.1.2, 1.2.0, 1.2.1&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This was tested on 1.1.2 and 1.2.0 on emulator.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Thanks to the smart &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/members/1630162"&gt;LordBubbles&lt;/a&gt; for helping me figure a couple things out!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Let me know if you run into any issues!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If you wanna hit me up or try to pull a phishing scam or something, you can message me on Discord @ therealprincesszelda</description>
