    <item>
      <title>Shimamura Yū JP Voice for Player (TotK Version)</title>
      <author>Jrhall2</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/558817</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/558817#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">c1faa914d9b10551b7f028e59257689bad28f2a1</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 28 Nov 2024 00:11:09 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6747b43eaf7b2.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6747b476917c9.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is a player voice replacement mod that is really meant to go alongside the TSP mod, but that can go with anything you so desire! For the sake of safety given recent-ish events, I will not be naming that mod directly, but you should check out the Discord that centers on a certain playable princess to learn more about the TSP mod.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This mod completely replaces Link's voice with Zelda's Japanese voice. All clips are from Zelda's official voice actress, Shimamura Yū, and were primarily sourced from AoC (though a small few clips were taken from BotW and TotK). Many of the player voice clips were repurposed from my BotW version of this project, though obviously new ones were also edited and created for all the new sounds Link has in this game. Of all the voice clips I drew from for this project, I further edited many of them myself to better fit the context of the actions. All clips that I edited were sourced from the original games, however - no outliers or exceptions. All I did was cut and/or repurpose certain pieces of them as I believed appropriate.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;All 337 player voice files, the special inn cutscenes, and (to my knowledge) every cutscene that contained Link's voice have been replaced with context-appropriate audio clips which I have taken extreme care with while editing and balancing. I compared each and every one to Link's original audio to match volume and intent as closely as possible and further replaced several after playtesting them in game to make sure the audio matched the new actions. Each file was deliberately and carefully selected to fit the action being displayed on screen from a collection of more than 300 voice clips I managed to isolate for use from all three games. I tell you all that to illustrate this point - this mod is meant to make it sound like you're *actually* playing as Zelda and I've taken extraordinary care to make sure your immersion isn't shattered by any audio choice I made.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I did take a few liberties to let a bit more of Zelda's personality shine through when compared to Link but nothing that detracts from player experience or that immersion. That is to say, not all clips are exact 1-to-1 replacements for Link's audio (for example, the way Zelda soothes the horse she's riding and the "humming" while she cooks are different mostly due to limitations of voice clips available), but the intent and purpose of the sounds remains consistent for each and every replacement. Most notably, Zelda has no instances of singing or humming in any official capacity, so I was unable to match each "cooking song." Instead, she has several different utterances of excitement or happiness as she cooks in order to achieve a similar variety of sound as Link's songs without sacrificing the quality of the voice replacement or the intent of the actions.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;i class="SelectedElement"&gt;A few particular notes about the project (if you're not interested, you can skip the green text - BUT DON'T SKIP THE RED TEXT):&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;I have been unable to test all the cutscene edits myself. I've only made sure that my replacement process was successful but I don't have save files that put me in a convenient position to test each cutscene (and I've been waiting to replay the game until TSP existed in a playable iteration). So while I'll be listening and watching for instances of cutscenes that might still have Link's voice in my own playthrough, please let me know if you catch any Link sounds that occur while the Zelda model is on screen that managed to evade me and I would be happy to replace it and add it to this project!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;One other thing worth noting is that one of the spear charging sounds is just broken in the base game (PV011_01 for anyone who's interested). Though Link opens his mouth to make a sound, he never makes this noise in game. In fact, TotK has a number of issues in the way the base, unmodded game calls on Link's player voice audio. Several sounds are outright missing in-game - the aforementioned standing spear charge sounds, both sounds that should be called when frozen solid by ice, and the sounds for fire based damage are called correctly when you're actually on fire but ALSO when you take launch damage that knocks you off your feet from any enemy or object. There are supposed to be four sounds that play there variably but none of them are appropriately called. Instead, launch damage calls PV303_00 and PV303_01 (both of the fire damage sounds) for some strange reason.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is an implementation issue with the base game so unfortunately I cannot make any of those sounds work as of now (at least not with my limited knowledge). So even though those files are included in this mod, if you're standing still and you charge a spear, there's a 50/50 chance Zelda will be silent sometimes just like the unmodded game. Also you'll be silent when you freeze solid. The fire damage has been taken into account, but sadly the cute touch of having Zelda say "atsui" (the Japanese word for "hot") when she catches on fire had to be cut to fix this.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is also *not* a "plot" immersion mod, simply a "player character" immersion mod. In terms of game plot, outside of in-engine cutscene vocalizations, nothing else has been edited - no instances of other characters using the name "Link" have been removed (that would be way too many languages for me to want to tackle myself), no prerendered cutscenes have even been touched (like the very first Ganondorf awakening cutscene), etc. It's just too much to do for a voice replacement mod.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I have also not touched a single line of text. I don't know how to change text (lol) so be aware that this is *only* a voice replacement - there's not a name/pronoun text replacement bundled with it. All that said, if you are planning to use this with the TSP mod, a lot of that will already be accounted for.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Finally, I do not play this game in English but I recognize the majority of people here likely do, maybe even with a Japanese Zelda voice mod. Let me know if something is off during the cutscenes especially - I think I have a handle on which files belong where in order to properly replace the cutscene audio (which isn't the easiest thing to intuit, I'll admit), but there's a chance I missed something obvious. In fact, let me know if this is true for any language outside of Japanese (which I'll be testing myself) - all selectable voice languages have been given the same cutscene audio replacement treatment in this mod and I want to make sure they work for everyone who wants them!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;ONE FINAL NOTE - I HAVE TESTED THIS WITH THE TSP MOD MYSELF BUT THERE MIGHT BE ISSUES GIVEN THE NATURE OF BOTH ITS RELEASE AND MY OWN MOD'S IMPLEMENTATION. PLEASE FOLLOW INSTRUCTIONS CAREFULLY TO MINIMIZE CHANCES OF PROBLEMS WHEN COMPILING THESE TWO MODS TOGETHER.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;u&gt;How to Install:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;Switch -&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Place *only* the romfs folder in atmosphere/contents/0100F2C0115B6000&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;FOR TSP COMPATABILITY - you will need to overwrite any files that already exist in the TSP mod folder for this to work properly, which you should be prompted to do on placing the folder on the SD card (if it's already been installed on your SD card).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;b&gt;Yuzu/Sudachi -&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Place the entire "Shimamura Yū Voice for Player Character" folder in yuzu/load/0100F2C0115B6000 OR sudachi/load/0100F2C0115B6000&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;FOR TSP COMPATABILITY - open the "Shimamura Yū Voice for Player Character" folder, take the "romfs" folder inside, and merge it with the TSP base mod's "romfs" folder (make a backup of the original mod before you do this). You will be prompted to overwrite several hundred files. Say yes and ONLY the voice files that pertain to the player character will be replaced. This WILL make the voice replacement work with the mod, no RSTB editing required from there. There might be some bugs or issues here and there, I have not fully tested this myself yet.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;Ryujinx -&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Place the entire "Shimamura Yū Voice for Zelda (Japanese Voice - TotK Full Version)" folder in Ryujinx/mods/contents/0100F2C0115B6000&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;FOR TSP COMPATABILITY - open the "Shimamura Yū Voice for Player Character" folder, take the "romfs" folder inside, and merge it with the TSP base mod's "romfs" folder (make a backup of the original mod before you do this). You will be prompted to overwrite several hundred files. Say yes and ONLY the voice files that pertain to the player character will be replaced. This WILL make the voice replacement work with the mod, no RSTB editing required from there. There might be some bugs or issues here and there, I have not fully tested this myself yet.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;I am very proud of the way this mod turned out despite the difficulties I had putting it together! I was very thorough but I wouldn't be surprised at all if I didn't catch everything on a first pass so please let me know if you notice any issues - I would be happy to keep updating this until it's the best version of the project it can be (though if there are updates to make, they may take some time as I am not very well versed in the process anymore compared to when I started this in 2023).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;No RSTB edits are required to use the full version of this mod and it should, in theory, work without flaw on every version of the game (I've tested it on 1.1.1, 1.1.2, and 1.2.0). If you are compiling it with the TSP mod, it should work perfectly if you overwrite the existing sounds within the TSP mod "romfs" folder with the "romfs" folder found in this download. There should be no issue there at all and the game should launch normally regardless of platform from there.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;If there is an issue with TSP launching after installing this voice mod alongside it, it likely isn't because of the file overwrite. There is probably a conflict between another mod (I had this issue myself during testing).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;There are also two versions to choose from when downloading - a version with an extra CUTSTOM cutscene included with the TSP mod and a version that is exclusively for the base game cutscenes without that extra TSP edit. Make sure to check the version descriptions to ensure you download the one you want!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;I really hope you enjoy! Have fun adventuring as Zel!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/shimamurayuvoiceforplayer_tspcustomcutscene.zip" type="application/zip"/>
