      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/67424e786a559.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/67424e1f732e1.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/67424e2714387.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6744f82687922.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; Older Versions&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Addition&lt;/em&gt;: Added older version files to main release file&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;This adds a standalone armor set and themed buster sword to the game. Each piece has base defense of 20 and it was put over the Evil Spirit set. It has full functionality of that original set plus some bonus effects added...&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Head - Attack Up, Lightning Proof, Stealth Up&lt;br&gt;Upper - Gloom Resist, Skydive Mobility Up, Stealth Up&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Lower - Climb Speed Up, No-Slip, Stealth Up&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;These effects are not visible on the menu screen but they are there working in the background (can verify with the gloom resist hearts that appear once upper equipped).&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The sword has 60 attack, Attack Up when health low, and Charge Speed Up, it will also cut trees, and is unbreakable. I had to make the sheath invisible due to collision with the cape and it just overall not looking good with any type of sheath I tried to use. There is some collision with the cape/sword when it is on his back as well. There are mods out there that can re-position the sheath so if you want to look into that, try &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/482367"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Armor and Sword can be purchased from a easily located Moogle in Lookout Landing for next to nothing!&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Special Credit goes to &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/members/2850833"&gt;PotatoFried17&lt;/a&gt; for use of his Moogle from his recent mods. They have released other Final Fantasy themed armors so go &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/557215"&gt;check them out&lt;/a&gt; they are great!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This was built and tested on 1.2.1 using Ryujinx and should work on any version, older version files included in 1.3 release or can use TKMM&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Cape has physics, hair does not (yet, but will in an update down the road once I get it looking right)&lt;br&gt;I am also working on getting physics added in for the 2 bandages that normally hang/dangle around the hilt of the blade so that it looks as close to authentic as possible.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I also added an image on this page to show moogle location in case you are having trouble finding him.</description>
